          <legend>Biographical Information</legend>
          <dl class="dl-horizontal">
            <dt>1949</dt>
            <dd>Herb Staehr born in Hartford, Connecticut.</dd>
            <dt>1969</dt>
            <dd>Attends the Woodstock Festival, where he first hears Ten Years After.</dd>
            <dt>2001</dt>
            <dd>Publishes Alvin Lee and Ten Years After: A Visual History.</dd>
            <dt>2008</dt>
            <dd>Dies of cancer.</dd>
          </dl>
          <p>
            Herb Staehr was a collector of photographs and memorabilia related to the English blues-rock band Ten Years
            After, who performed at Woodstock in 1969. He was the author of Alvin Lee and Ten Years After: A Visual
            History, regarded as the definitive work on the band.
          </p>
          <h6>Sources</h6>
          <p>
            "Tribute to Herb Staehr -- Historian of the Band Ten Years After." Ten Years After. 
            Accessed May 13, 2011. http://www.ten-years-after.com/herb/tribute.htm.
          </p>
          <legend>Separated Materials</legend>
          <p>
            Commercially released CDs, videocassettes, and audiocassettes have been transferred to the library collection.
            Please search for the "Herb Staehr Collection" in the library catalog for a list of donated titles. If you are
            unable to find what you are looking for, consult the Library and Archives staff to ensure these materials are
            available.
          </p>
          <legend>Custodial History</legend>
          <p>
            The Herb Staehr Collection was received by the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame and Museum, Inc. as a gift from Thomas
            W. and Claudia Staehr on December 8, 2008.
          </p>
        </div>

